1
00:00:01,637 --> 00:00:04,470
(Multicom Jingle)

2
00:00:13,284 --> 00:00:16,034
(dramatic music)

3
00:00:42,980 --> 00:00:46,063
(train horn blowing)

4
00:01:04,865 --> 00:01:07,448
(upbeat music)

5
00:01:24,307 --> 00:01:27,390
(train horn blowing)

6
00:01:33,325 --> 00:01:35,908
(soft chatter)

7
00:01:41,587 --> 00:01:44,170
(upbeat music)

8
00:02:03,664 --> 00:02:06,171
- [Rainie] Billy, wake up.

9
00:02:06,171 --> 00:02:09,171
(upbeat band music)

10
00:02:21,589 --> 00:02:24,422
(excited chatter)

11
00:02:26,814 --> 00:02:30,814
("The Army Goes Rolling Along")

12
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:51,953
- We're home?

13
00:02:51,953 --> 00:02:53,036
- We're home.

14
00:02:56,242 --> 00:02:59,325
(train horn blowing)

15
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:07,523
(people applauding and cheering)

16
00:03:28,817 --> 00:03:31,650
(people cheering)

17
00:03:32,739 --> 00:03:35,322
(upbeat music)

18
00:03:57,954 --> 00:03:59,817
- [Sara] Billy!

19
00:03:59,817 --> 00:04:00,650
- Sara!

20
00:04:01,930 --> 00:04:02,763
- [Sara] Billy!

21
00:04:02,763 --> 00:04:03,596
- Sara!

22
00:04:03,596 --> 00:04:04,763
Oh, oh my God!

23
00:04:06,483 --> 00:04:08,160
Look at you.

24
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,527
- [Sara] Oh Billy.

25
00:04:09,527 --> 00:04:10,718
- Oh God.

26
00:04:10,718 --> 00:04:12,260
- I missed you so much.

27
00:04:12,260 --> 00:04:14,730
- Look at you, I leave
you alone for four years

28
00:04:14,730 --> 00:04:18,070
and look what happens to
you, you've grown up on me.

29
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:20,430
Rainie when I saw her
last she was a skinny,

30
00:04:20,430 --> 00:04:24,214
freckle-faced girl,
now look at her, golly.

31
00:04:24,214 --> 00:04:26,660
She's a knockout, isn't she a knockout?

32
00:04:26,660 --> 00:04:27,783
- [Rainie] Knocked me out.

33
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:31,367
- Wait, where's grandpa?

34
00:04:31,367 --> 00:04:34,367
- Grandpa's not doing so good Billy.

35
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:36,700
- I wanna go see him.

36
00:04:37,583 --> 00:04:38,815
- Let's go.

37
00:04:38,815 --> 00:04:40,972
- [Billy] Well how'd you get here?

38
00:04:40,972 --> 00:04:42,007
- I drove.

39
00:04:42,007 --> 00:04:43,840
- You're driving now!

40
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,804
- Yeah, so next week I get
to take the training wheels

41
00:04:45,804 --> 00:04:46,726
off my bicycle.

42
00:04:46,726 --> 00:04:47,800
- God, okay.

43
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,633
- Say you mind if I catch a ride

44
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:50,789
to the bus station with y'all?

45
00:04:50,789 --> 00:04:51,960
- It's okay with me if you don't mind

46
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:53,260
riding with a baby sister.

47
00:04:54,410 --> 00:04:56,480
- Be my baby any day.

48
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,221
- You're Rainie Pritchard aren't ya?

49
00:04:58,221 --> 00:04:59,837
- [Rainie] The one and only.

50
00:04:59,837 --> 00:05:01,033
- That's Stumpy?

51
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:02,032
- That's Stumpy.

52
00:05:02,032 --> 00:05:03,710
- [Rainie] That's what
they used to call me.

53
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:08,350
- Boy this place has sure built up

54
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:10,113
since the last time I was here.

55
00:05:12,110 --> 00:05:13,640
So you're a college girl now, huh?

56
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:15,160
- If I don't get through this trig course

57
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,010
I won't be for long.

58
00:05:16,010 --> 00:05:17,491
- What college are you going to?

59
00:05:17,491 --> 00:05:18,491
- Centenary.

60
00:05:19,370 --> 00:05:21,070
- Isn't that expensive?

61
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,708
- I'm on a scholarship.

62
00:05:22,708 --> 00:05:24,135
- For what?

63
00:05:24,135 --> 00:05:24,968
- Choir.

64
00:05:24,968 --> 00:05:26,044
- Watch where you're going.

65
00:05:26,044 --> 00:05:27,300
- I see him.

66
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:30,307
- Choir, they give scholarships for that?

67
00:05:30,307 --> 00:05:32,640
(chuckling)

68
00:05:39,590 --> 00:05:42,963
So, how come you haven't
asked me about my leg yet?

69
00:05:45,781 --> 00:05:47,114
- What happened?

70
00:05:51,117 --> 00:05:52,034
- Iwo Jima.

71
00:05:54,487 --> 00:05:57,193
Caught a slug right below the knee.

72
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:03,840
I woulda bled to death if old Rainie here

73
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,190
hadn't pulled me to safety.

74
00:06:10,211 --> 00:06:12,211
- They couldn't save it?

75
00:06:13,550 --> 00:06:15,350
- They didn't even have time to try.

76
00:06:16,430 --> 00:06:19,253
Not with all the casualties
they were tending to.

77
00:06:23,379 --> 00:06:24,779
You know what that's called?

78
00:06:27,671 --> 00:06:29,280
What?

79
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:31,630
Rainie you know exactly
what I'm talking about.

80
00:06:33,903 --> 00:06:34,883
It's called triage.

81
00:06:38,243 --> 00:06:39,576
- What's triage?

82
00:06:40,783 --> 00:06:43,150
- Well let's say you
got a boy in a stretcher

83
00:06:43,150 --> 00:06:47,200
with a chest wound and
in the next stretcher

84
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,500
you got someone else
with a severe head wound,

85
00:06:50,690 --> 00:06:53,013
well the doctors are gonna
treat the chest wound,

86
00:06:54,030 --> 00:06:55,680
because the poor sap that
got shot in the head,

87
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:56,980
well he's a gonner anyhow.

88
00:06:59,310 --> 00:07:00,910
And if you've got a mangled leg,

89
00:07:02,449 --> 00:07:03,282
well it's a heck of a lot easier

90
00:07:03,282 --> 00:07:04,820
to take a hacksaw to it than it is

91
00:07:04,820 --> 00:07:08,583
to piece it together again, that's triage.

92
00:07:11,667 --> 00:07:14,117
And that's what happened
to my leg little sister.

93
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:17,813
And that is what the war is all about.

94
00:07:19,097 --> 00:07:22,371
(dramatic music)

95
00:07:22,371 --> 00:07:23,871
- I'm sorry Billy.

96
00:07:24,830 --> 00:07:27,003
- We're home Billy, we made it.

97
00:07:29,970 --> 00:07:31,270
So what's for supper Sara?

98
00:07:48,114 --> 00:07:50,281
(snoring)

99
00:07:58,051 --> 00:07:59,551
- [Billy] Grandpa.

100
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:01,593
Grandpa.

101
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,650
- Who's that?

102
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:06,720
- Hey, it's me, Billy.

103
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,600
- [Will] Billy?

104
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,433
- Yeah.

105
00:08:10,260 --> 00:08:11,093
- Billy!

106
00:08:13,348 --> 00:08:16,200
Oh my goodness my boy, good to see you!

107
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:17,900
How are ya, you made it home did ya?

108
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:18,733
Let me look at ya.

109
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:19,610
- [Billy] I did, I made it back.

110
00:08:19,610 --> 00:08:23,170
- My golly, look at them medals
and stripes, and everything,

111
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:24,130
how in the world are you?

112
00:08:24,130 --> 00:08:25,553
- [Billy] I'm good, how are you?

113
00:08:25,553 --> 00:08:27,480
- Well I'm fine as frog's hair.

114
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:30,490
- Oh, that's not what I hear.

115
00:08:30,490 --> 00:08:31,690
- Who's this fella here?

116
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:34,040
- Rainie Pritchard, sir.

117
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:37,773
- You remember Rainie, from back home?

118
00:08:38,790 --> 00:08:40,300
We were in the same outfit together.

119
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:42,370
- He's the one that saved Billy's life.

120
00:08:42,370 --> 00:08:46,040
- Why I sure do, welcome
here my boy, good to see ya.

121
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:48,049
- [Sara] Grandpa now, let's
not get yourself too worked up,

122
00:08:48,049 --> 00:08:49,049
boys let's let grandpa.

123
00:08:49,049 --> 00:08:50,840
- Now wait a minute, they just got here.

124
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,587
- You'll see plenty of them after supper,

125
00:08:52,587 --> 00:08:53,836
now I'll bring yours in directly.

126
00:08:53,836 --> 00:08:55,384
- You will not, I'm getting up,

127
00:08:55,384 --> 00:08:57,151
I'm having supper at the table.

128
00:08:57,151 --> 00:08:59,373
(upbeat music)

129
00:08:59,373 --> 00:09:00,206
- Come on.

130
00:09:02,804 --> 00:09:04,020
(laughing)

131
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:05,610
- Rainie let me get you
another piece of pie.

132
00:09:05,610 --> 00:09:07,760
- No, no, no I can't, I'm full.

133
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:09,340
- Oh, come on you've only had two.

134
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:11,410
- Billy, will you do something
about your little sister,

135
00:09:11,410 --> 00:09:12,243
she's killing me.

136
00:09:12,243 --> 00:09:14,080
- I can't help you there buddy,

137
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,480
she's got a mind of her own.

138
00:09:16,990 --> 00:09:18,960
- I'll have a piece of that pie.

139
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:21,110
- Grandpa, you know
you can't have any pie.

140
00:09:24,175 --> 00:09:25,625
- You can't control the girl.

141
00:09:26,830 --> 00:09:28,603
- Well I don't think she's all that tough.

142
00:09:30,690 --> 00:09:32,500
- Well you just might be surprised.

143
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,623
- You never can tell.

144
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,360
Say, anybody know what time it is?

145
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,193
- I do!

146
00:09:41,310 --> 00:09:42,143
Quarter to 9:00.

147
00:09:43,703 --> 00:09:47,140
- The last bus leaves at
9:30, I better be going.

148
00:09:47,140 --> 00:09:49,320
- Oh I can get you there, but
we'd have to leave right now.

149
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,660
- [Rainie] You don't mind?

150
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:51,833
- No, no, not at all.

151
00:09:56,027 --> 00:09:57,640
- [Rainie] Sorry I gotta
eat and run partner.

152
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:58,910
- Well you want me to go with ya?

153
00:09:58,910 --> 00:09:59,880
- [Sara] Oh, no thanks Billy.

154
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:02,111
- No, no, that's okay, I'll be happy to.

155
00:10:02,111 --> 00:10:03,777
- No thanks, Billy.

156
00:10:03,777 --> 00:10:04,610
- Nice seeing you Mr. Coleman.

157
00:10:04,610 --> 00:10:06,090
- Good to meet you sir.

158
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:07,350
- Take care.

159
00:10:07,350 --> 00:10:08,560
- I'll be back soon.

160
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:09,974
- [Will] You drive carefully you hear?

161
00:10:09,974 --> 00:10:11,141
- [Sara] Okay.

162
00:10:17,892 --> 00:10:20,092
- Well, what's the matter with you?

163
00:10:20,092 --> 00:10:20,925
(scoffing)

164
00:10:20,925 --> 00:10:22,593
- You're just gonna let her go like that?

165
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:24,383
- Why not?

166
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:31,680
- Grandpa, Rainie's my best
friend, but that doesn't mean

167
00:10:31,810 --> 00:10:34,593
I like that fact that
he's with Sara, alone.

168
00:10:35,910 --> 00:10:38,490
I've seen this guy in action,

169
00:10:38,490 --> 00:10:40,163
and I don't mean the battlefield.

170
00:10:41,330 --> 00:10:42,980
- I don't think you're
giving your little sister

171
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:44,594
enough credit, she's a
grown woman you know.

172
00:10:44,594 --> 00:10:48,770
- I know, and that's what worries me.

173
00:10:48,770 --> 00:10:51,963
- Don't worry, she can
take care of herself.

174
00:10:54,108 --> 00:10:57,380
Now I'm going out on the
porch, why don't you bring

175
00:10:57,380 --> 00:10:58,853
your coffee and come with me?

176
00:11:03,990 --> 00:11:04,823
- Gosh, it sure feels good

177
00:11:04,823 --> 00:11:06,260
to drive a car after all this time.

178
00:11:09,980 --> 00:11:12,380
It's funny the things you
miss when you're away.

179
00:11:16,730 --> 00:11:21,023
- I read your letter and
I'm sorry about your leg.

180
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:27,020
You know, they tell me
that the coon hunting

181
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:29,930
around here is number one.

182
00:11:29,930 --> 00:11:30,945
- Is that so?

183
00:11:30,945 --> 00:11:33,130
(chuckling)

184
00:11:33,130 --> 00:11:35,240
Well, I haven't been coon
hunting in a long time grandpa,

185
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,513
not since I was a kid.

186
00:11:38,432 --> 00:11:39,265
(soft music)

187
00:11:39,265 --> 00:11:41,363
- Maybe it's about time
you tried it again?

188
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:46,603
- No, I don't think so, not with this leg.

189
00:11:51,249 --> 00:11:52,082
- Billy,

190
00:11:53,770 --> 00:11:55,520
you remember when you was a young fella

191
00:11:57,489 --> 00:11:59,750
and you had a tough time saving
up the money for that dog,

192
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:01,357
what was it Red Boy?

193
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:04,683
- Old Dan and Little Ann.

194
00:12:07,020 --> 00:12:08,890
- You remember how we
talked about you making

195
00:12:08,890 --> 00:12:11,790
a deal with God, and how
if he held up his end

196
00:12:11,790 --> 00:12:14,573
of the bargain you'd meet him halfway?

197
00:12:16,730 --> 00:12:20,200
Did you do that, did you meet him halfway?

198
00:12:21,978 --> 00:12:23,311
How do you know?

199
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:27,533
- 'Cause I got my dogs.

200
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:33,417
- No different now you know?

201
00:12:36,043 --> 00:12:37,603
Just gotta meet him halfway.

202
00:12:41,050 --> 00:12:43,380
Would you be at all interested in

203
00:12:45,810 --> 00:12:47,910
looking and seeing what's out in the barn?

204
00:12:48,966 --> 00:12:50,128
(chuckling)

205
00:12:50,128 --> 00:12:51,663
- You better not have.

206
00:12:56,361 --> 00:12:59,897
- Welcome home my boy, this
old man's going to bed.

207
00:13:01,730 --> 00:13:03,433
- Grandpa, come on.

208
00:13:05,386 --> 00:13:06,219
- What?

209
00:13:06,219 --> 00:13:07,110
- I'm not gonna go stumbling around

210
00:13:07,110 --> 00:13:10,010
in the dark just to check out the barn.

211
00:13:10,010 --> 00:13:12,910
- There's a lantern
hanging right on the corner

212
00:13:12,910 --> 00:13:13,743
of the house.

213
00:13:15,941 --> 00:13:18,070
- [Billy] What about the yard is it level?

214
00:13:18,070 --> 00:13:21,343
- No sir, it's bumpy,
it's bumpy all the way.

215
00:13:23,810 --> 00:13:25,543
There's nothing guaranteed you know?

216
00:13:27,540 --> 00:13:29,260
- You're messing with me old man.

217
00:13:58,679 --> 00:14:01,262
(upbeat music)

218
00:14:13,672 --> 00:14:15,503
- Well Sara, thank you for the ride.

219
00:14:15,503 --> 00:14:18,263
And you take care of that
no good brother of yours.

220
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:20,773
- When will we see you again?

221
00:14:22,304 --> 00:14:24,313
Billy would wanna know.

222
00:14:25,771 --> 00:14:26,840
- Well that depends.

223
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:27,740
- Depends on what?

224
00:14:29,323 --> 00:14:31,223
- If we're gonna go out Saturday night.

225
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:37,823
- Saturday, Saturday let me see.

226
00:14:39,828 --> 00:14:41,178
- I'll pick you up at 8:00.

227
00:15:13,810 --> 00:15:14,813
- Old man.

228
00:15:17,126 --> 00:15:17,959
Oh boy I'm gonna drown you

229
00:15:17,959 --> 00:15:20,374
if you're messing with me tonight.

230
00:15:20,374 --> 00:15:22,791
(soft music)

231
00:15:44,402 --> 00:15:47,485
(puppies whimpering)

232
00:16:02,407 --> 00:16:04,740
(chuckling)

233
00:16:06,733 --> 00:16:08,233
I don't need this!

234
00:16:09,252 --> 00:16:11,835
(upbeat music)

235
00:16:20,144 --> 00:16:21,771
(scoffing)

236
00:16:21,771 --> 00:16:24,638
(chuckling)

237
00:16:24,638 --> 00:16:25,758
Look at this.

238
00:16:25,758 --> 00:16:29,758
Huh, look at this, yeah
you like that don't you?

239
00:16:31,251 --> 00:16:32,084
Great.

240
00:16:34,872 --> 00:16:37,396
You ready to go out, huh?

241
00:16:37,396 --> 00:16:38,646
You ready to go out with me?

242
00:16:38,646 --> 00:16:39,479
Come here.

243
00:16:42,585 --> 00:16:44,433
I don't have time for this.

244
00:16:44,433 --> 00:16:49,433
Come here you, come on.

245
00:16:54,707 --> 00:16:56,803
(sighing)

246
00:16:56,803 --> 00:16:58,633
Come on get back in.

247
00:17:01,052 --> 00:17:02,852
You're gonna drive me nuts, no stay.

248
00:17:06,270 --> 00:17:11,270
Get in there, get back down,
you're gonna drive me crazy.

249
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:12,593
Get in, come on.

250
00:17:14,039 --> 00:17:17,523
There you go, get your tail off.

251
00:17:17,523 --> 00:17:18,485
Get in there.

252
00:17:18,485 --> 00:17:21,213
(chuckling)

253
00:17:21,213 --> 00:17:23,463
I don't have time for this!

254
00:17:24,657 --> 00:17:25,490
Come on.

255
00:17:30,820 --> 00:17:33,153
(chuckling)

256
00:17:41,083 --> 00:17:42,600
- Well he knew the trouble we went to

257
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:45,143
to get the dogs for you,
not to mention the money.

258
00:17:47,151 --> 00:17:49,270
Think of all the clothes
I could've bought.

259
00:17:49,270 --> 00:17:52,947
- Sara, I'm sorry okay, but
you should've asked me first.

260
00:17:52,947 --> 00:17:55,510
I mean I don't want the dogs,

261
00:17:55,510 --> 00:17:57,323
I don't need the responsibility.

262
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:03,040
Look, it was a very sweet
thing that you and grandpa did

263
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:06,771
but I just I can't have
it, it's not gonna work.

264
00:18:06,771 --> 00:18:08,730
- It wasn't something me and grandpa did,

