524
00:35:49,220 --> 00:35:50,840
To be treated as a different person.

525
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:52,210
What would your daddy
have done if he caught

526
00:35:52,210 --> 00:35:53,540
another man being rough with your mom?

527
00:35:53,540 --> 00:35:54,660
- He woulda killed them.

528
00:35:54,660 --> 00:35:55,783
- [Billy] That's right.

529
00:35:56,830 --> 00:35:57,663
- Billy!

530
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:01,113
Look,

531
00:36:02,330 --> 00:36:04,663
we've been through a
long, hard fight together.

532
00:36:06,560 --> 00:36:08,270
And even though our side
won I don't feel like

533
00:36:08,270 --> 00:36:11,613
much of a winner, and I
know you don't either.

534
00:36:14,072 --> 00:36:15,122
I mean all that pain.

535
00:36:17,860 --> 00:36:18,693
The killing.

536
00:36:21,010 --> 00:36:23,440
Just when you think this
world is this horrible,

537
00:36:23,440 --> 00:36:25,350
terrible place to live
someone like your sister

538
00:36:25,350 --> 00:36:26,960
comes into your life
and it doesn't seem like

539
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:28,653
such a terrible place after all.

540
00:36:33,510 --> 00:36:37,580
- Well don't tell that to
me Rainie, tell that to her.

541
00:36:37,580 --> 00:36:40,023
(dramatic music)

542
00:36:40,023 --> 00:36:41,253
Want me to shoot him?

543
00:36:43,340 --> 00:36:45,493
I'll be happy to beat
him up if you want me to?

544
00:36:47,260 --> 00:36:51,840
- No thanks, but I'll
holler if I need you.

545
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:53,423
- Okay, you do that.

546
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:04,063
Rainie listen to me, okay?

547
00:37:05,910 --> 00:37:07,420
I can't speak for Sara,

548
00:37:07,420 --> 00:37:09,240
she's old enough to
make her own decisions.

549
00:37:09,240 --> 00:37:12,720
But, if you treat her

550
00:37:13,820 --> 00:37:15,943
anything less than the Queen of England,

551
00:37:17,410 --> 00:37:19,010
Lord help me boy I'm
gonna put a hurt on you

552
00:37:19,010 --> 00:37:21,423
kerosene won't wash off,
do you understand me?

553
00:37:23,836 --> 00:37:28,836
- Yes sir, Sergeant.

554
00:37:34,144 --> 00:37:35,327
Sara, listen.

555
00:37:35,327 --> 00:37:39,200
- No, you listen, and
you listen good buster.

556
00:37:39,200 --> 00:37:43,713
If you ever wanna kiss me
again, you ask me first.

557
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:48,733
And if I say yes, which I don't often do.

558
00:37:49,858 --> 00:37:51,870
Then I want you to give me

559
00:37:51,870 --> 00:37:55,860
a short, sweet, gentlemen like kiss.

560
00:37:55,860 --> 00:38:00,860
Not one of those wet,
slobbery, bathe my face kisses.

561
00:38:06,531 --> 00:38:07,531
- Like that?

562
00:38:09,372 --> 00:38:11,250
- You didn't ask me first.

563
00:38:11,250 --> 00:38:13,417
(sighing)

564
00:38:14,285 --> 00:38:16,202
- Sara, may I kiss you?

565
00:38:19,213 --> 00:38:20,213
- I suppose.

566
00:38:36,814 --> 00:38:38,064
- Is that okay?

567
00:39:13,860 --> 00:39:14,760
- Howdy neighbor.

568
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:16,400
- Howdy, how are ya?

569
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:17,320
Homer Jeffries.

570
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:19,631
- Billy Coleman, pleased to meet you sir.

571
00:39:19,631 --> 00:39:20,464
- [Homer] This is my son Wilson.

572
00:39:20,464 --> 00:39:21,297
- Hi.

573
00:39:22,230 --> 00:39:25,300
- You know we only live just
a mile and a 1/2 up the road.

574
00:39:25,300 --> 00:39:28,540
- Yes sir, I know, I've seen
you pass by a couple of times.

575
00:39:28,540 --> 00:39:30,793
My grandfather speaks
very highly of you sir.

576
00:39:31,850 --> 00:39:32,803
- Billy, how is he?

577
00:39:34,420 --> 00:39:37,350
- Well, with all things
considering I'd say

578
00:39:37,350 --> 00:39:39,350
he's doing quite well, thanks.

579
00:39:39,350 --> 00:39:42,273
- Anyhow, the reason why I
stopped is to ask you a favor.

580
00:39:44,130 --> 00:39:46,160
My boy here has been driving me crazy

581
00:39:46,160 --> 00:39:48,568
to stop here and see if you might let him

582
00:39:48,568 --> 00:39:50,143
take a look at them dogs.

583
00:39:51,471 --> 00:39:52,304
(chuckling)

584
00:39:52,304 --> 00:39:53,137
- Is that so.

585
00:39:53,137 --> 00:39:54,450
(dog barking)

586
00:39:54,450 --> 00:39:56,443
Well sure, come on down, be my guest.

587
00:39:57,860 --> 00:39:59,680
- Wilson, just a couple of minutes now,

588
00:39:59,680 --> 00:40:00,610
we gotta get into town.

589
00:40:00,610 --> 00:40:01,711
- Yes, sir.

590
00:40:01,711 --> 00:40:02,544
- Okay.

591
00:40:02,544 --> 00:40:03,740
- How are you Wilson?

592
00:40:03,740 --> 00:40:05,135
Pleased to meet ya.

593
00:40:05,135 --> 00:40:05,968
- Redbones?

594
00:40:05,968 --> 00:40:08,170
- You bet, you a coon hunter?

595
00:40:08,170 --> 00:40:09,003
- You bet.

596
00:40:10,330 --> 00:40:11,353
- You got some dogs?

597
00:40:12,740 --> 00:40:13,573
- No, sir.

598
00:40:17,770 --> 00:40:20,740
- Tell me something Wilson,
is there coom back in here?

599
00:40:20,740 --> 00:40:22,870
- You bet, if you know where to look.

600
00:40:22,870 --> 00:40:25,370
- Yeah, do you know where to look?

601
00:40:25,370 --> 00:40:28,090
- Well, yes, sir, I go
hunting and trapping

602
00:40:28,090 --> 00:40:30,230
just about every night,
and I do all right.

603
00:40:30,230 --> 00:40:32,281
Do a lot better if I
had me some dogs though.

604
00:40:32,281 --> 00:40:34,698
(soft music)

605
00:40:37,545 --> 00:40:39,340
- You know I've been training these dogs

606
00:40:39,340 --> 00:40:42,850
for quite some time now,
and I was thinking about

607
00:40:42,850 --> 00:40:44,800
taking 'em out tonight.

608
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:47,250
You see, I don't get along
very well on this leg,

609
00:40:47,250 --> 00:40:49,763
and I was hoping I could get some help.

610
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:52,670
Think maybe you'd like
to come along with me?

611
00:40:52,670 --> 00:40:55,070
- Yes, sir, you mean it?

612
00:40:55,070 --> 00:40:57,853
- You bet, why don't you go ask your pa?

613
00:41:07,666 --> 00:41:10,675
- I'm so excited, I hope
they do good for you.

614
00:41:10,675 --> 00:41:11,940
- Well being that it's their first time,

615
00:41:11,940 --> 00:41:13,770
I'm not expecting too much.

616
00:41:13,770 --> 00:41:15,506
Could you pack another
one of those please?

617
00:41:15,506 --> 00:41:16,339
- [Sara] Oh sure.

618
00:41:16,339 --> 00:41:17,172
- Thanks.

619
00:41:23,040 --> 00:41:23,940
- Where you going?

620
00:41:24,810 --> 00:41:28,000
- I'm taking the dogs
out tonight, first time.

621
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:30,133
You know your neighbor, Mr. Jeffries?

622
00:41:31,029 --> 00:41:33,730
He stopped by today and
I asked his son Wilson

623
00:41:33,730 --> 00:41:35,540
to come along with me.

624
00:41:35,540 --> 00:41:36,540
- Oh, that's nice.

625
00:41:36,540 --> 00:41:37,373
- Yeah.

626
00:41:39,200 --> 00:41:40,750
- You're not gonna be too late.

627
00:41:43,060 --> 00:41:45,500
- Well no, I don't think I'll be.

628
00:41:45,500 --> 00:41:46,333
Why?

629
00:41:48,900 --> 00:41:51,450
- Well, I think tomorrow
morning I'll go to church.

630
00:41:54,206 --> 00:41:55,039
(chuckling)

631
00:41:55,039 --> 00:41:57,010
- All right, would you
like me to go with you?

632
00:41:59,890 --> 00:42:00,840
- Yes I would.

633
00:42:02,687 --> 00:42:03,520
You too.

634
00:42:04,970 --> 00:42:05,803
- Yes, sir.

635
00:42:07,420 --> 00:42:10,733
- Good, well good hunting,

636
00:42:12,660 --> 00:42:13,493
and goodnight.

637
00:42:21,780 --> 00:42:25,197
- He looks really tired,
doesn't he look tired to you?

638
00:42:26,423 --> 00:42:29,110
I mean do you think he's
gonna be up to getting dressed

639
00:42:29,110 --> 00:42:31,286
and going to church tomorrow?

640
00:42:31,286 --> 00:42:32,613
- I think it'd be good for him.

641
00:42:34,540 --> 00:42:37,900
I was thinking about asking
Rainie to go to church with us.

642
00:42:37,900 --> 00:42:38,733
- Hmm.

643
00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:42,453
Gee, I haven't seen much
of my ex-best buddy.

644
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:44,950
Is everything okay?

645
00:42:46,100 --> 00:42:47,563
- He is so nice.

646
00:42:51,356 --> 00:42:52,189
Have fun.

647
00:42:52,189 --> 00:42:53,022
Thank you.
- Be careful.

648
00:42:55,840 --> 00:42:59,020
- Well, you look like you're about ready.

649
00:42:59,020 --> 00:42:59,853
- Yes, sir.

650
00:42:59,853 --> 00:43:00,686
- Hold this.

651
00:43:00,686 --> 00:43:02,140
How is my gang doing tonight?

652
00:43:02,140 --> 00:43:05,120
Little Ann you're looking
very, very pretty.

653
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:07,868
And Old Dan, you're the
dignified gentlemen, isn't he?

654
00:43:07,868 --> 00:43:08,701
- Yes, sir.

655
00:43:08,701 --> 00:43:10,560
- I'm counting on you
two, let's not forget

656
00:43:10,560 --> 00:43:12,880
what I've been teaching ya, huh?

657
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:15,430
You ready to do a little
hunting tonight, huh?

658
00:43:15,430 --> 00:43:17,200
- Yes, sir, Little Ann
looks about ready to go.

659
00:43:17,200 --> 00:43:19,893
- Yeah, she sure is,
okay, grab your lantern.

660
00:43:21,510 --> 00:43:24,120
Now, Wilson, hold on.

661
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:25,820
Wilson, see there very fired up?

662
00:43:25,820 --> 00:43:27,130
- Yep.

663
00:43:27,130 --> 00:43:28,720
- This is why you have to
listen to me at all times.

664
00:43:28,720 --> 00:43:30,893
It's very important, hey, back!

665
00:43:33,510 --> 00:43:35,010
You have to listen to me at all times,

666
00:43:35,010 --> 00:43:37,146
that is first and foremost,
you understand me?

667
00:43:37,146 --> 00:43:37,979
- Yes, sir.

668
00:43:37,979 --> 00:43:39,550
- Okay, that's why I
invited you to come along,

669
00:43:39,550 --> 00:43:41,740
to experience this, and the second thing,

670
00:43:41,740 --> 00:43:43,720
you must remain quiet, okay?

671
00:43:43,720 --> 00:43:46,370
Do not speak unless you're
spoken to, is that clear.

672
00:43:46,370 --> 00:43:48,122
- [Wilson] Yes, sir.

673
00:43:48,122 --> 00:43:50,400
- All right, now I was gonna
let you handle the dogs tonight

674
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:51,850
but you gotta be able to pull them back

675
00:43:51,850 --> 00:43:52,916
whenever you have to.

676
00:43:52,916 --> 00:43:53,749
- Yes, sir.

677
00:43:53,749 --> 00:43:54,715
- You can't let them run
off on you like that.

678
00:43:54,715 --> 00:43:55,548
- Yes, sir.

679
00:43:55,548 --> 00:43:56,430
- Okay, come on back Dan.

680
00:43:56,430 --> 00:43:57,580
Think you can do it?

681
00:43:57,580 --> 00:43:58,413
- Yes, sir.

682
00:43:58,413 --> 00:43:59,380
- Okay, you hold onto here.

683
00:44:00,736 --> 00:44:02,550
And give me the lantern.

684
00:44:02,550 --> 00:44:04,143
Hey, are you a good runner?

685
00:44:05,700 --> 00:44:08,690
- Yes, sir, pretty good.

686
00:44:08,690 --> 00:44:12,400
- Pretty good, come on
Wilson, this isn't a time

687
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:14,530
for laziness now, there's
a lot of endurance

688
00:44:14,530 --> 00:44:15,363
involved in this.

689
00:44:15,363 --> 00:44:16,720
Come on, suck in your stomach boy!

690
00:44:16,720 --> 00:44:18,180
Pull back those shoulders.

691
00:44:18,180 --> 00:44:19,665
You gonna be able to run with my dogs?

692
00:44:19,665 --> 00:44:20,498
- Yes, sir.

693
00:44:20,498 --> 00:44:21,331
- I can't hear you.

694
00:44:21,331 --> 00:44:22,201
- Yes, sir!

695
00:44:22,201 --> 00:44:23,280
- Let's do ourselves a little hunting.

696
00:44:23,280 --> 00:44:24,113
Woo hoo!

697
00:44:25,050 --> 00:44:25,883
Let's go!

698
00:44:31,614 --> 00:44:32,790
That a boy.

699
00:44:32,790 --> 00:44:35,373
(upbeat music)

700
00:44:46,197 --> 00:44:49,293
Give 'em a ya-hoo every once in a while.

701
00:44:49,293 --> 00:44:50,126
- Ya-hoo!

702
00:44:53,180 --> 00:44:55,158
- You gotta work on that Wilson.

703
00:44:55,158 --> 00:45:00,158
- [Wilson] Yes, sir.

704
00:45:04,247 --> 00:45:06,830
(dogs barking)

705
00:45:22,742 --> 00:45:25,825
(raccoon chittering)

706
00:45:41,364 --> 00:45:42,197
- They got one?

707
00:45:42,197 --> 00:45:43,030
- Sure sounds like it.

708
00:45:43,030 --> 00:45:44,270
- What do you want me to do?

709
00:45:44,270 --> 00:45:46,610
- Okay, I want you to
run as fast as you can

710
00:45:46,610 --> 00:45:48,310
and follow 'em, and when you find 'em

711
00:45:48,310 --> 00:45:50,085
you stay with them until I get there.

712
00:45:50,085 --> 00:45:50,918
- [Wilson] Yes, sir.

713
00:45:50,918 --> 00:45:51,751
- Okay, get going.

714
00:46:02,754 --> 00:46:04,254
- [Wilson] Ya-hoo!

715
00:46:08,188 --> 00:46:09,021
- Ya-hoo!

716
00:46:10,943 --> 00:46:13,693
(dramatic music)

717
00:46:18,031 --> 00:46:19,531
- Great, now what?

718
00:46:20,675 --> 00:46:22,758
Mr. Coleman, Mr. Coleman!

719
00:46:26,556 --> 00:46:28,806
(groaning)

720
00:46:37,036 --> 00:46:37,869
- Damn.

721
00:46:52,498 --> 00:46:54,748
(groaning)

722
00:47:02,900 --> 00:47:05,483
(dogs barking)

723
00:47:23,625 --> 00:47:24,802
(dramatic music)

724
00:47:24,802 --> 00:47:26,254
Wilson!

725
00:47:26,254 --> 00:47:30,337
- [Wilson] Sir, over here,
I'm just ahead of you.

726
00:47:32,306 --> 00:47:35,190
- Come on I thought you
said you were a coon hunter?

727
00:47:35,190 --> 00:47:36,290
You gotta keep moving.

728
00:47:37,150 --> 00:47:37,983
- Which way?

729
00:47:41,071 --> 00:47:43,077
- There, there are the tracks, that way.

730
00:47:44,290 --> 00:47:46,433
That a boy, you gotta tough it out now.

731
00:47:49,106 --> 00:47:50,773
Woo, way to go team!

732
00:47:52,272 --> 00:47:53,105
Huh?

733
00:47:53,105 --> 00:47:55,610
You got 'em in the tree?

734
00:47:55,610 --> 00:47:59,693
Way to go team, okay let's
get the leashes ready.

735
00:48:00,810 --> 00:48:01,643
Way to go Dan,

736
00:48:03,250 --> 00:48:04,083
my boy!

737
00:48:06,047 --> 00:48:07,560
(laughing)

738
00:48:07,560 --> 00:48:09,603
How do ya like that, first time out!

739
00:48:12,030 --> 00:48:13,030
- [Wilson] Now what?

740
00:48:15,160 --> 00:48:19,193
- Well, looks like we're just
gonna have to wait 'em out.

741
00:48:20,170 --> 00:48:22,020
Either that or cut down the tree.

742
00:48:22,020 --> 00:48:23,120
- I've got my hatchet.

743
00:48:24,100 --> 00:48:24,933
(chuckling)

744
00:48:24,933 --> 00:48:26,130
- That little thing?

745
00:48:26,130 --> 00:48:27,250
No, we'd be down here all week long

746
00:48:27,250 --> 00:48:29,701
cutting this tree down with that.

747
00:48:29,701 --> 00:48:30,534
You know?

748
00:48:30,534 --> 00:48:33,284
When I was your age I used
to have a hatchet like that.

749
00:48:34,180 --> 00:48:35,700
First time I went out coon hunting,

750
00:48:35,700 --> 00:48:40,450
came up to a big tree like
this and I was cutting away

751
00:48:40,450 --> 00:48:42,652
all night long, I got so tired.

752
00:48:42,652 --> 00:48:43,980
(chuckling)

753
00:48:43,980 --> 00:48:45,780
Grandfather gave me heck for it too.

754
00:48:47,916 --> 00:48:49,398
We just have to sit down and wait 'em out,

755
00:48:49,398 --> 00:48:50,810
that's the only thing we can do.

756
00:48:50,810 --> 00:48:53,460
And that's liable to
take quite a spell too.

757
00:48:53,460 --> 00:48:54,810
Let's see what time we got here.

758
00:48:54,810 --> 00:48:57,763
Way to go team, I'm so proud of you!

759
00:49:02,411 --> 00:49:03,328
It's 10:30!

760
00:49:08,060 --> 00:49:09,270
I promised my grandfather

761
00:49:09,270 --> 00:49:11,170
I'd take him to church in the morning.

762
00:49:12,320 --> 00:49:13,163
- Church?

763
00:49:14,410 --> 00:49:17,970
- Wilson, I gave him my
word, I've gotta keep it.

764
00:49:17,970 --> 00:49:20,569
- But you gave your word to them too.

765
00:49:20,569 --> 00:49:22,120
- I know.

766
00:49:22,120 --> 00:49:23,620
- [Wilson] I'll stay with 'em.

767
00:49:25,670 --> 00:49:27,350
- What, I'm supposed
to give you the rifle?

768
00:49:27,350 --> 00:49:28,183
- Yes, sir.

769
00:49:32,220 --> 00:49:34,193
- Have you ever shot one of these before?

770
00:49:35,420 --> 00:49:36,333
- [Wilson] You bet.

771
00:49:40,870 --> 00:49:43,330
- Well, you know Wilson there's no telling

772
00:49:43,330 --> 00:49:46,260
how long this ringtail's
gonna stay holed up in here.

773
00:49:46,260 --> 00:49:48,680
I mean you could be here all night long.

774
00:49:48,680 --> 00:49:50,710
- Yes sir, but doesn't that also mean

775
00:49:50,710 --> 00:49:52,423
it could be 15 minutes from now?

776
00:49:55,320 --> 00:49:56,153
- Well,

777
00:49:57,120 --> 00:49:58,220
you got a point there.

778
00:49:59,196 --> 00:50:01,703
But it's more likely you're
gonna be here all night long.

779
00:50:03,590 --> 00:50:05,060
Okay.

780
00:50:05,060 --> 00:50:06,863
All right, now look.

781
00:50:08,360 --> 00:50:11,250
This is not a toy, you understand me?

782
00:50:11,250 --> 00:50:12,083
- Yes, sir.

783
00:50:14,020 --> 00:50:16,370
- Now, hold it, put it in your hands.

784
00:50:16,370 --> 00:50:19,400
Now you see here, this is the safety.

785
00:50:19,400 --> 00:50:22,390
Okay, you keep that pressed in
when you're not gonna use it.

